---
title: "Pain modulates early sensory brain responses to task-irrelevant emotional faces"
collection: publications
#permalink: 'https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1002/ejp.2097'
#excerpt: 'This paper is about the number 2. The number 3 is left for future work.'
date: 2023-02-20
venue: 'European Journal of Pain'
#paperurl: "https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1002/ejp.2097/"
#citation: 'Xu, Q., Ye, C., Li, X., Zhao, G., & Astikainen, P. (2023). Pain modulates early sensory brain responses to task‐irrelevant emotional faces. European Journal of Pain.'
---
In this paper, we found that lab-induced pain can alter both featural (reflected by P1) and structural face-sensitive (reflected by N170) visual encoding responses of emotional faces, even when the faces are irrelevant to the task.


[Download paper here](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1002/ejp.2097/)


Recommended citation: Xu, Q., Ye, C., Li, X., Zhao, G., & Astikainen, P. (2023). Pain modulates early sensory brain responses to task‐irrelevant emotional faces. <i>European Journal of Pain.</i>, DOI: 10.1002/ejp.2097  
